  "body": "# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nThis is a large tracking issue for improving the security of Prysm as well as enhance \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n**High Level**\r\n- [x] Resolve deep source analysis issues, especially those with bug risks attached to them\r\n- [x] Resolve race detection issues with go test all across Prysm\r\n- [x] Harden dependencies, update relevant ones which had bug fixes\r\n\r\n**Repository Health**\r\n- [x] Remove deprecated tools from the repository and clean up READMEs\r\n\r\n**Go Code Improvements**\r\n- [x] Complete integration of most go vetting tools, such as ineffassign along with important static analyzers for safety\r\n- [ ] Reduce high amount of interface redundancy, making it difficult for outsiders to step in\r\n- [ ] Make certain packages more \"pure\", akin to the core package. For example, we should isolate eth2-specific logic and code paths from service and business logic codepaths\r\n- [ ] Many different variants of duplicated code: FuncWithNoBLSVerify, FuncWithBLSVerify, obfuscates the process to reason about for others\r\n- [ ] Caches are mixed with important functions and should be more isolated, such as cache filling occurring somewhere different than where it was needed\r\n- [ ] All cache keys should be audited to ensure they are used properly\r\n\r\n**Accounts and Validator RPC**\r\n- [x] Use a different password than the wallet password for logging in through the web interface for security purposes\r\n- [x] No need to expose DefaultWalletPath endpoint, in-fact, such endpoint is not even needed\r\n- [x] Logout should invalidate JWT in backend\r\n- [x] JWT auth path should have more tests and should enforce a signing type provided by the token from the user\r\n- [x] Consider not exposing the backup endpoint at all via RPC, as it is too high-risk if an attacker gains access\r\n- [x] Disable account creation for non-HD wallets, and rename it to `imported` wallet to align with the web UI. For security reasons, this type of wallet should only be able to import external keystores\r\n- [x] If someone has never signed up before, someone else could sign up for a staker if they gain access to the validator RPC \r\n- [x] Remove accounts-v1 in favor of accounts-v2 only\r\n- [x] Slashing protection should be clear-cut and documented for users to understand its implications",
